  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p><em>From <a href="https://code.google.com/u/109067824594513388759/">thilo.mu...@gmail.com</a> on July 15, 2011 10:28:26</em></p>

<p>Thank you for your report. Support for rendering of road numbers is not yet implemented in the mapsforge map library, although the idea is not new (see for example issue <a href="https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/issues/143" class="issue-link" title="optimized colors &amp; signs">#143</a> ). It will definitely be added sooner or later, as having these information is very important and a standard feature in other maps.</p>

<p><a href="https://github.com/J" class="user-mention">@J</a>ürgen: does the mapfile writer already store the value of the ref tag in binary map files so that it could be extracted and rendered by the map library? Or are some adjustments required here as well?</p>

<p><strong>Status:</strong> Accepted<br><br>
  <strong>Owner:</strong> <a href="mailto:thilo.mu...@gmail.com">thilo.mu...@gmail.com</a><br><br>
  <strong>Cc:</strong> <a href="mailto:jjbross@gmail.com">jjbross@gmail.com</a><br><br>
  <strong>Labels:</strong> -Type-Defect Type-Enhancement  </p>
