  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p><em>From <a href="https://code.google.com/u/109067824594513388759/">thilo.mu...@gmail.com</a> on April 05, 2012 06:20:52</em></p>

<p>In revision r2000 i have added a few rules to the default render-theme to display road numbers on motorways. Unfortunately the visual quality is quite bad because there is no collision detection yet in place to avoid overlapping road names and numbers (see issue <a href="https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/issues/43" class="issue-link" title="Improve label placement algorithm">#43</a> ). So the attached screenshot displays rather a best-case scenario, the average case is worse.</p>

<p>In the current render-theme API there is also no possibility to periodically add a horizontal caption/symbol on a way, therefore the road number is always drawn along the way. Other render applications like Mapnik usually draw a nice horizontal sign with the road number on top, which is also my preferred solution (see for example here: <a href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/?lat=52.62484&amp;lon=13.43405&amp;zoom=15&amp;layers=M">http://www.openstreetmap.org/?lat=52.62484&amp;lon=13.43405&amp;zoom=15&amp;layers=M</a> ).</p>

<p><strong>Status:</strong> Started  </p>

<p><strong>Attachment:</strong> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/mapsforge/issues/detail?id=154#hc5">road_numbers_demo.png</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

